NO-Show DATA SET¶

This project is based on the 'noshowappointments-kagglev2-may-2016.csv' file that showed a number of patients that didn't show up at the doctors appointment

Make no_show to show and values to 0s and 1s so we can aggregate no numeric types

Final Conclusions¶

  1. Schedulations have been between 0 and 179 days which is the same day of appointments and 3 months before
  2. Most people Attended were those who scheduled the same day and the ratio of attendance decrease gradually as the day difference increases
  3. Most Patients were females
  4. The older the patients the more careful they are about their health
  5. 24% of scholars didn't attend their appointments, which means that being enrolled in scholarship programs doesn't seem to make people likely to show up
  6. People who are alcoholic tend to be less careful about their lives
  7. The more the people have illness conditions they are more likely to come except for those having more than 4 illness conditions
  8. Hypertensions patients are the most to attend out of all conditions
  9. SMS reminders didn't affect people to show up, the graphs show that people who have received SMS have a reliable number of not showing up

Limitations¶

  1. Strong correlations don't exist since data is categorical
  2. All statistics were descriptive
